    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        void initialize(java.util.List<Attributes> attributesList,
                Topography topography,
                AttributesAgent attributesPedestrian,
                java.util.Random random)
        This method initializes this model by selecting the appropriate attributes from the list and creating sub models. It also sets attributes recursively for its sub models.

      • findAttributes

        static <T extends Attributes> T findAttributes(java.util.List<Attributes> attributesList,
                                               java.lang.Class<T> type)
        Searches for Attributes class of given type. If no object is found this method throws a AttributesNotFoundException. If multiple instances of the given class exist a AttributesMultiplyDefinedException is thrown.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the actual class type.
        Parameters:
        attributesList - List of all available Attributes.
        type - the Attributes class type to search for.
        Returns:
        Attributes instance with searched type T.
